    <section>
        <title>Integration with the gate / intercom</title>
        <para>
            The gate functions as simply another terminal, with extension <literal>24</literal>.
            Once a call has been initiated with the gate (either by dialing it's number, or by
            picking up a call from the gate intercom) it is opened and closed by entering the
            code <literal>1 3 1</literal> on your telephone.
        </para>
        <note>
            <para>
                On non-digital extensions (terminals other than those at reception or Fritz's office) the
                <literal>FLASH</literal> button needs to be pressed before entering the open/close code.
            </para>
        </note>
    </section>

